MECHANISM
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Each transaction is encoded NOT as its 166 flat features but as a case
of graph-neighbourhood typology terms over a licit/illicit lattice:
  - fanIn_* / fanOut_*  : predecessor / successor degree class
  - inVal_* / outVal_*  : incoming / outgoing value tier
  - temp_*              : temporal-step bucket (49 steps -> early/mid/late)
  - nbrIllicit_* / nbrLicit_* : neighbour LABEL context (leak-guarded:
      train-visible labels only; a node's OWN class is never emitted)
Higher-order relations flowsFrom(fanIn, nbrCtx) and flowsTo(fanOut, nbrCtx)
wire the node's own topology to its neighbour context — the cross-record
structure flat-tabular encodings discard. SMA mounts the lattice and
retrieves illicit analogs by structural match; dense/BM25 see the same
term text; logreg sees the raw 166 features (the flat-tabular control).
Evaluation: retrieval-by-analogy kNN (k=15) — vote retrieved analogs'
known labels into an illicit score; metric = macro-F1 + ROC-AUC.

